Solar "T.strahl": Kraft von 5000 Sonnen!

Eric Jacobmain
Der Solarkonzentrator R5800, der durch den neuen R23k ersetzt wurde, besteht aus einer gewöhnlichen Glasfaser-Satellitenschüssel. Es ist mit etwa 5800 3/8" (~1cm) Spiegelkacheln bedeckt. Bei richtiger Ausrichtung kann es einen Fleck von der Größe eines Cents mit einer Intensität von 5000 mal normalem Tageslicht erzeugen. Diese Lichtintensität ist mehr als genug, um zu schmelzen Stahl verdampfen, Aluminium verdampfen, Beton kochen, Schmutz in Lava verwandeln und jedes organische Material im Handumdrehen auslöschen. Es ist 5 Fuß 9 Zoll groß und hat einen Durchmesser von 42 Zoll. Leider wurde der R5800 bei einem Lagerschuppenbrand am 14. Dezember vollständig zerstört , 2010, etwa 8 Monate nach Dreh dieses Videos, wurde durch den R23k ersetzt, der 23.000 Spiegel und eine Konzentrationskraft von 10.000 mal Tageslicht hat _ Musik: „hypnothis“ www.incompetech.

If the British were ready to partially unlock the funds of Russian banks for "mercenaries", then what kind of mercenaries are these?

It can be assumed that the "mercenaries" that presidents and prime ministers ask for are integrated into the economic strategies of states and elites.

One can recall how persistently Emmanuel Macron tried to get through to the President of Russia during the blockade of Azovstal, and how he requested an emergency call on September 20.

Most of all, the British could be interested in the release of those who were captured in an attempt to capture the Zaporozhye nuclear power plant and the IAEA mission.

The visit of the IAEA mission took place with the support of France.

September 20 Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation A.V. Grushko
received the Ambassador of the French Republic to the Russian Federation Pierre Levy.

On the Russian side... attention is focused on the unacceptability of further inflation of Ukraine
Western, incl. and French, weapons that the Kyiv regime uses to shell civilian and infrastructure facilities, including the Zaporozhye nuclear power plant.

The father of the Deputy Foreign Minister Viktor Grushko was the first deputy head of the PGU (intelligence) of the KGB (1983-1989), the head of the VGU (counterintelligence) of the KGB (1989-1991), the first deputy chairman of the KGB (January-August 1991).

Pierre Levy was ambassador to the Czech Republic and Poland.

Perhaps Macron wanted to prevent those who were captured from being handed over to the UK. The failure of MI6 may have been due to French intelligence.

Now the released pro-saboteurs may be a threat to the interests of France, for example, in the transit Niger. Or elsewhere in the world.

Specifically, these specialists will no longer be on the territory of Ukraine, but they still have the motive to work for their intended purpose [against the interests of France].

Why could the Kremlin decide that now London (and MI6) is preferable to Paris (and DGSE)?

Perhaps France was too actively involved in the aggravation of the situation before the SCO summit, including the offensive of the Armed Forces of Ukraine in the Kharkiv region.

Perhaps the UK has become more receptive to proposals after the threat to ArcelorMittal in Krivoy Rog.

Giving impetus to the weakened side, Russia step by step uses the conflicts in the NATO bloc, "destroying alliances."

Unblocked funds can find a worthy use to support the interests of Russia.

Returning to the events in Mariupol, when Macron needed to decide something with the evacuation.

The destruction of Azovstal is assessed differently in London and Paris.

The resignation of the head of French military intelligence, Eric Vido, could be associated with mistakes in Mariupol.

In April, the capture of American General Roger Cloutier was also reported, whose activities in Africa intersected (perhaps in conflict) with those of Vido.

On August 4, General Darryl Williams, who previously served as commander of the US Ground Forces in Europe and Africa, was appointed to the post of Cloutier (head of NATO Land Command).
As for Cloutier - silence.

Williams' predecessor, General Christopher Cavoli, was promoted to head of US European Command.

Cavoli and Williams are the curators of the offensive of the Armed Forces of Ukraine in the Kharkiv region.

Williams' deputy in NATO Land Command is Italian General Nicola Zanelli. Former commander of the MTR of Italy. He was Deputy Commander of NATO Forces in Afghanistan, replacing British General Giles Hill in December 2020.

The withdrawal of NATO troops from Afghanistan in August 2021 was the responsibility of Zanelli.
Probably, for him, the issues of drug trafficking are far from terra incognita.

Cavoli, Williams and Cloutier at various times served at the American base in the Italian Vicenza (Venice region). All are related to missions in Africa.

Cavoli served in Afghanistan as Deputy Commander of Regional Command West (RCW) in Herat Province. The commanders of the RCW were Italian generals.
